definition.value: An organophosphate oxoanion that is the trianion of (2E)-4-hydroxy-3-methylbut-2-enyl diphosphate arising from deprotonation of the three OH groups of the diphosphate.
A nucleotide conjugate consisting of CDP joined at the 1-position of valienol via a diphosphate linkage.
An organophosphate oxoanion that is the trianion of isopentenyl diphosphate arising from deprotonation of the three OH groups of the diphosphate.
A long-chain fatty acid that is octadecanoic (stearic) acid substituted at positions 12 and 18 by hydroxy groups.
